1
00:00:01,133 --> 00:00:02,833
<i> This is the area.
</i>This is where we'll find Father.

2
00:00:02,833 --> 00:00:04,200
<i> I can't be wrong.</i>

3
00:00:04,267 --> 00:00:06,833
<i>- He's still there, hurry up.
- Yes, ma'am.</i>

4
00:00:06,833 --> 00:00:08,767
[GRUNTS]

5
00:00:08,767 --> 00:00:09,800
<i> Who's that guy?</i>

6
00:00:09,933 --> 00:00:11,300
I encountered him on the island

7
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:13,100
<i>when we were arresting
Datu Rahman.</i>

8
00:00:13,233 --> 00:00:14,833
<i> He was supposed to help
Datu Rahman escape,</i>

9
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:16,333
<i>but the kidnappers
got to him first.</i>

10
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:18,633
<i>We need to find him
to know the truth.</i>

11
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:20,067
Let's proceed to Barangay Surga.

12
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:21,533
Isn't that the Muslim community?

13
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:24,733
Omar, there are people outside!
<i> They look like the police!</i>

14
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:25,867
<i> I know a doctor!</i>

15
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:28,100
<i>She's nice, but she
follows the law strictly.</i>

16
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:30,067
<i> Doctor, you know me...</i>

17
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:31,900
<i> I wouldn't harbor a criminal.</i>

18
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,467
<i> Jalil isn't a bad person.</i>

19
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:34,800
<i> Thank you very much.</i>

20
00:00:34,967 --> 00:00:37,400
<i>My son is on his way home.
He works for the SID.</i>

21
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:38,933
<i>He comes from the same place
as Datu Rahman.</i>

22
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:41,067
He can answer all my questions.

23
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:43,933
<i>Why are you picking
fights with a kid?!</i>

24
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:46,767
<i>Are you on our side,
or are you working for them?</i>

25
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,967
<i>We believe that you're
not a bad person.</i>

26
00:00:48,967 --> 00:00:51,400
Don't worry. We'll protect you.

27
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:52,633
<i> Thank you.</i>

28
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:54,600
- [TIRES SCREECH]
- [CAR HONKING]

29
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:57,433
<i>- Hi, Dad.
- [TENSE MUSIC STINGS]</i>

30
00:00:57,433 --> 00:01:00,167
<i>Welcome back, Agent Reyes.
Your suspension has been lifted.</i>

31
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:01,833
Maybe you could give me a tour?

32
00:01:01,967 --> 00:01:04,800
<i>So I could get to know
my new neighbors.</i>

33
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,600
<i>Wait a minute...
you're the police!</i>

34
00:01:06,833 --> 00:01:09,067
- [SCREAMS]<i> Aah!
</i>- Go ahead, come close!

35
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:11,033
<i> Bring the criminal out now!</i>

36
00:01:11,033 --> 00:01:13,633
<i>We're not allowed to harbor
criminals. Please leave.</i>

37
00:01:13,733 --> 00:01:15,533
<i>- Go away!
- Go away!</i>

38
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:16,867
<i>- Leave!
- Leave!</i>

39
00:01:16,867 --> 00:01:18,300
<i> I can't stay here long.</i>

40
00:01:18,367 --> 00:01:20,133
<i>You'll all be in danger
because of me.</i>

41
00:01:20,333 --> 00:01:23,333
<i>Omar told me about you.
I owe him a lot.</i>

42
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:25,233
<i>- You're just in luck.
- [METAL DOOR RATTLES]</i>

43
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:26,500
<i> This place is empty.</i>

44
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:28,767
<i> My friend knows someone.</i>

45
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,700
He said he saw a van coming out
<i> of the Greenmile Warehouse.</i>

46
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:33,000
<i> I'm tracking Datu Rahman.</i>

47
00:01:33,167 --> 00:01:35,367
<i>I need to find him to prove
that I didn't help him escape.</i>

48
00:01:35,733 --> 00:01:37,133
<i> I'm at the ZylveriX Building.</i>

49
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:39,100
<i>I know where they're hiding
Datu Rahman.</i>

50
00:01:39,300 --> 00:01:41,700
<i>Didn't I tell you to tell me
your every move?!</i>

51
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:47,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:54,900
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

53
00:02:03,533 --> 00:02:04,767
[PHONE THUDS]

54
00:02:04,767 --> 00:02:07,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:09,567
Dispatch, this is Agent Angeles.

56
00:02:09,567 --> 00:02:11,600
I need backup
in the ZylveriX Building.

57
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,533
There's a possible
hostile situation.

58
00:02:13,533 --> 00:02:17,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

59
00:02:17,967 --> 00:02:20,667
- [FELIX SIGHS]
- [DOOR CLICKS OPEN]

60
00:02:23,767 --> 00:02:25,000
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN]

61
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:32,900
[SIREN WAILING]

62
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:39,133
[CAR DOOR OPENS, SLAMS]

63
00:02:39,133 --> 00:02:41,567
I need men inside!
Check the van.

64
00:02:42,433 --> 00:02:43,600
Where's Datu Rahman?

65
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:46,400
[FELIX] What?
Did we lose him, sir?

66
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,800
They've escaped
with Datu Rahman!

67
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,233
They beat us to it again.

68
00:02:50,467 --> 00:02:57,433
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:03:09,167 --> 00:03:10,733
[LARA] If you had
told me sooner,

70
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:12,333
I could have sent
someone right away.

71
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:13,800
Lara, the intel came in
out of nowhere.

72
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,233
I had to move fast!

73
00:03:15,233 --> 00:03:16,733
You're bypassing me!

74
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:19,633
You broke the chain of command!
Aren't I your Head Agent?!

75
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:22,233
And this recklessness!
This isn't you!

76
00:03:22,433 --> 00:03:23,667
You used to be sharp!

77
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:27,133
Our enemy is sharp.
They've outsmarted us again.

78
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,367
This is what I've been saying!

79
00:03:29,367 --> 00:03:30,667
Get your head in the game!

80
00:03:30,867 --> 00:03:32,100
Really, Lara?

81
00:03:32,533 --> 00:03:34,267
You could've followed me with--

82
00:03:34,267 --> 00:03:35,167
With what?!

83
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:38,800
With what?!

84
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:46,833
Nothing.

85
00:03:47,367 --> 00:03:49,467
We need to catch Datu Rahman.

86
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:52,467
I've said it many times!
We need to catch him

87
00:03:52,467 --> 00:03:55,633
because that's the only reason
Director Azuelo

88
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:57,933
agreed to my request
to reinstate you.

89
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:04,367
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN, SLAMS]

90
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:08,100
[MUSIC STINGS]

91
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:10,233
We need to find
this bastard.

92
00:04:10,233 --> 00:04:11,533
We'll easily earn
two million if we find him!

93
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:14,400
- That's a big amount of money.
- He's just here somewhere.

94
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:19,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

95
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:20,767
Isn't that him?

96
00:04:22,067 --> 00:04:24,033
- I think it's him.
- Don't be suspicious.

97
00:04:24,733 --> 00:04:26,667
We'll follow him once
he passes us.

98
00:04:26,667 --> 00:04:28,633
- Okay.
- It might be him.

99
00:04:30,067 --> 00:04:31,333
Let's go.
We need to follow him.

100
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:33,667
Slowly.

101
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:40,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

102
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,567
Got you!

103
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,567
My bad! I'm sorry!

104
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,833
[MAN 1] This guy
isn't easy to find.

105
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:02,933
[MAN 2] You're right.

106
00:05:03,067 --> 00:05:04,900
[MAN 3] He has a long beard.

107
00:05:05,233 --> 00:05:06,867
They all looked alike!

108
00:05:10,967 --> 00:05:17,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:05:32,967 --> 00:05:40,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

110
00:05:43,633 --> 00:05:45,633
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GRUNTS] Argh!

111
00:05:47,467 --> 00:05:52,567
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

112
00:05:59,133 --> 00:06:06,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

113
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:07,933
<i> I knew it.</i>

114
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:10,900
[LAPTOP SLAMS]

115
00:06:11,467 --> 00:06:13,067
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

116
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:16,133
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

117
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:17,333
Sir.

118
00:06:18,467 --> 00:06:19,267
Oh.

119
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:21,567
Where's Datu Rahman?

120
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,300
Haven't got him yet?

121
00:06:24,533 --> 00:06:25,800
Then, why are you here?

122
00:06:26,667 --> 00:06:29,067
Shouldn't you be out there
looking for him?

123
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:31,800
Sir, I need your help.

124
00:06:32,867 --> 00:06:33,967
What kind of help?

125
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:36,967
I've given you
your gun and badge back.

126
00:06:37,267 --> 00:06:38,567
What else do you need?

127
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,900
Sir...

128
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:43,600
I need to show you something.

129
00:06:44,633 --> 00:06:47,000
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYS]

130
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:51,633
We were here, sir,
when the ambush happened.

131
00:06:51,867 --> 00:06:53,867
Before our comms
got intercepted.

132
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:58,200
Reyes, here you are again
with your interceptions.

133
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,667
Sir, please.

134
00:07:00,233 --> 00:07:01,767
Look at this.

135
00:07:06,067 --> 00:07:07,033
Sir...

136
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:09,600
When the gunfire started,

137
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:12,367
the bullets came from
the other side of the island.

138
00:07:12,733 --> 00:07:13,767
Look, sir.

139
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:15,867
Look at where
they're being shot from.

140
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:19,567
The bullet came from behind,
not from us.

141
00:07:20,533 --> 00:07:22,867
According to the ballistic
report of the bullets found

142
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:25,067
on the road where
Datu Rahman was kidnapped,

143
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,800
the same types of guns
were used in other crimes.

144
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,567
The same weapons.

145
00:07:32,567 --> 00:07:34,300
Coming from the same source.

146
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:43,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYS]

147
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,900
[SIGHS]

148
00:07:51,067 --> 00:07:52,767
It's a large syndicate.

149
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,533
So?

150
00:07:55,233 --> 00:07:56,433
Sir.

151
00:07:57,133 --> 00:08:00,333
The guns were military
and police grade.

152
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:02,200
What do you mean?

153
00:08:02,567 --> 00:08:05,333
It's not just from
gun smuggling operations.

154
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:08,533
Someone's helping them out
from our side.

155
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,733
What's going on with you, Reyes?

156
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:17,167
You're one of the best
intelligence officers in SID.

157
00:08:17,433 --> 00:08:21,700
You're not that kind of officer
who jumps into conclusions.

158
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,033
Sir...

159
00:08:25,167 --> 00:08:28,133
You said it yourself.
I'm one of the best.

160
00:08:29,633 --> 00:08:31,733
Just trust me, sir.

161
00:08:33,933 --> 00:08:36,933
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

162
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:43,233
Sir.

163
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:46,900
I went to the place where
they're hiding Datu Rahman.

164
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:49,600
But when I got there,
he was gone.

165
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,267
Not only do they have
Datu Rahman,

166
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:58,800
they also know our every move.

167
00:08:59,133 --> 00:09:02,233
Sir, we have an internal breach.

168
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:04,633
Nonsense!

169
00:09:04,867 --> 00:09:05,933
Reyes.

170
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:09,233
I will become General
in a few months.

171
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:11,067
I'm about to retire!

172
00:09:11,267 --> 00:09:14,600
I have a good pension
for my wife and children.

173
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,933
I can't risk that anymore.

174
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:20,300
Sir...

175
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:23,233
Sir, our hands are stained

176
00:09:24,133 --> 00:09:26,900
with the blood of the people
killed on the island.

177
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:30,000
Our friends and colleagues
were murdered!

178
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:33,400
Their families are
searching for answers!

179
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,967
Begging for justice!

180
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,433
My life is going great, Reyes.

181
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,300
Don't ruin it now.

182
00:09:41,967 --> 00:09:44,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:09:56,733 --> 00:09:57,533
Reyes.

184
00:10:09,733 --> 00:10:11,067
If you're wrong,

185
00:10:12,267 --> 00:10:14,000
your career is over.

186
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:18,233
But if you're right...

187
00:10:18,933 --> 00:10:21,333
Sir, we have an enemy

188
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:26,033
right inside NLEA and SID.

189
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,967
I'm about to retire.

190
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,033
Not right now, sir.

191
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:36,133
Our fight has only just begun.

192
00:10:46,033 --> 00:10:52,933
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

193
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:15,033
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:36,933
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

195
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:53,933
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

196
00:12:08,967 --> 00:12:15,933
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

197
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:25,200
[SCREAMS]

198
00:12:33,133 --> 00:12:35,967
- [GUNFIRE]
- [CRYING]

199
00:12:40,133 --> 00:12:42,500
<i> Daddy! Mommy!</i>

200
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,267
<i> Daddy!</i>

201
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:49,033
[SCREAMING IN FURY]

202
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:55,300
[LARA SCREAMS]

203
00:12:58,433 --> 00:13:02,100
- [CRUNCHES]
- [LARA SCREAMING CONTINUES]

204
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:03,333
[SMACKS]

205
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:08,033
[CRYING]

206
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:10,333
[SMACKS]

207
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:17,900
[CRYING, SNIFFLING]

208
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,233
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

209
00:13:20,233 --> 00:13:27,167
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

210
00:13:42,033 --> 00:13:49,000
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

211
00:14:01,567 --> 00:14:02,900
[DOOR LOCKS]

212
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:04,900
<i>Marcus and the others
are on their way.</i>

213
00:14:05,233 --> 00:14:06,700
<i> You know what to do, right?</i>

214
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:10,433
See to it that he won't be able
<i> to track down Datu Rahman.</i>

215
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:15,467
[LARA] See, Marcus?

216
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:18,067
<i> I'm always two steps ahead.</i>

217
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:24,967
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:14:25,567 --> 00:14:27,267
- [CAR HORN HONKING]
- [TIRES SCREECHING]

219
00:14:27,433 --> 00:14:28,200
Stupid!

220
00:14:28,467 --> 00:14:34,000
- [CAR ENGINE REVVING]
- [TIRES SCREECHING]

221
00:14:34,267 --> 00:14:35,300
What a sicko!

222
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,400
Zylverix?

223
00:14:39,767 --> 00:14:41,333
But it's already abandoned!

224
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,133
People still visit it?

225
00:14:45,033 --> 00:14:47,267
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

226
00:14:47,267 --> 00:14:49,667
[MOTORCYCLE ENGINE REVVING]

227
00:14:49,667 --> 00:14:52,333
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

228
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:59,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:02,967
[MARCUS] Sir, we were here

230
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:04,600
<i> when the ambush took place</i>

231
00:15:05,067 --> 00:15:07,000
<i>before our comms
were intercepted.</i>

232
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:11,167
<i>Reyes, there you go again
with all your interceptions.</i>

233
00:15:12,467 --> 00:15:13,967
[AZUELO] Reyes.

234
00:15:14,233 --> 00:15:16,800
<i>In a few months, I'll finally
become  a general.</i>

235
00:15:17,133 --> 00:15:18,600
<i> I can finally retire!</i>

236
00:15:20,033 --> 00:15:21,233
<i> I can leave my pension</i>

237
00:15:21,233 --> 00:15:23,200
<i>as a good asset
for my wife and kids!</i>

238
00:15:23,533 --> 00:15:25,300
<i> I can't risk anything anymore!</i>

239
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:30,400
[MARCUS]<i> Reputation, career,
</i> and family are the only things

240
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:31,633
<i> important to you.</i>

241
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:35,167
<i>You will do anything
to save yourself.</i>

242
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:42,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:15:57,033 --> 00:16:00,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

244
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:04,800
Whoever you are who is behind
all these killings and chaos,

245
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:09,467
I'll catch you soon enough.

246
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:16,100
- [CAR ENGINE REVVING]
- [TIRES SCREECHING]

247
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,533
[SEAT BELT UNBUCKLES]

248
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:26,500
[CAR ENGINE REVVING PASSING BY]

249
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:39,267
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

250
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:46,067
Mommy...

251
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:49,767
Daddy...

252
00:16:52,433 --> 00:16:54,233
Datu Rahman is finally
in my hands.

253
00:17:01,267 --> 00:17:03,367
I finally caught your murderer.

254
00:17:06,467 --> 00:17:13,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

255
00:17:15,767 --> 00:17:17,233
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

256
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:24,800
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:27,300
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

258
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:41,433
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

259
00:17:41,433 --> 00:17:48,400
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

260
00:17:58,300 --> 00:17:59,500
Jalil!

261
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:01,300
You're just on time!

262
00:18:01,633 --> 00:18:02,600
Let's eat!

263
00:18:04,567 --> 00:18:05,867
[DOOR CLOSES]

264
00:18:06,633 --> 00:18:08,667
[WHISPERING] Jamilah,
what are you doing here?

265
00:18:09,633 --> 00:18:11,833
Why? Can't I visit here, Jalil?

266
00:18:12,367 --> 00:18:13,867
What if someone sees you?

267
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:16,200
What if someone followed you?

268
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,300
Jalil, I just wanted
to make sure

269
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:20,600
that you're eating properly.

270
00:18:20,867 --> 00:18:22,867
Here, I brought you some food.

271
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:24,133
You shouldn't be here.

272
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:25,800
A lot of people
are looking for me.

273
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,733
It's why I left Uncle's place!

274
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:29,567
So that I won't drag
you all into this!

275
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:32,067
- [THUDS]
- You know what?

276
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:34,367
That's what I don't understand!

277
00:18:34,667 --> 00:18:36,333
Why are we the ones

278
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,633
who are hiding like mice?!

279
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:43,300
Jalil, they massacred
our village!

280
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:47,667
Why are we the ones hiding
as if we are the criminals?!

281
00:18:49,567 --> 00:18:50,900
Don't worry, Jamilah.

282
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,700
It'll all be okay.

283
00:18:53,433 --> 00:18:55,467
But first, I have
to find Father.

284
00:18:57,267 --> 00:18:59,333
Jamilah, listen to me.

285
00:18:59,867 --> 00:19:01,633
I don't want you to get hurt.

286
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:08,600
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:19:08,967 --> 00:19:10,733
[TRAFFIC NOISE]

288
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:12,733
[VEHICLES HONKING]

289
00:19:15,867 --> 00:19:22,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

290
00:19:22,633 --> 00:19:23,833
Marcus!

291
00:19:24,767 --> 00:19:27,100
[CHUCKLES] What's on your mind
this early in the morning?

292
00:19:29,267 --> 00:19:30,900
You're in a good mood.

293
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,467
Any good news?

294
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,633
No.

295
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:36,467
I've just been
feeling a lot better.

296
00:19:37,333 --> 00:19:38,267
Really?

297
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:40,900
Why, what happened?

298
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:43,067
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

299
00:19:43,067 --> 00:19:45,933
Nothing. I mean, you're back.

300
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:47,500
And it appears that
you and Dir. Azuelo

301
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:48,733
have resolved your differences,

302
00:19:48,733 --> 00:19:52,633
so our chances of finding
Datu Rahman are a lot higher.

303
00:19:54,467 --> 00:19:56,567
Everything's turning out
for the better, right?

304
00:19:58,633 --> 00:19:59,700
Yeah.

305
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,300
I'll see you around.

306
00:20:13,433 --> 00:20:18,667
[UNSETTLING MUSIC SWELLS, ENDS]

307
00:20:18,667 --> 00:20:25,600
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

308
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:28,700
This is your meeting place?

309
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:29,500
- Uncle.
- Jalil.

310
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,833
(In Arabic)
Peace be upon you.

311
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:33,767
- Jalil...
- Peace be upon you.

312
00:20:33,767 --> 00:20:34,667
Uncle.

313
00:20:35,967 --> 00:20:38,567
Jalil, I wanted to
follow your instructions

314
00:20:38,567 --> 00:20:40,533
to not bring anyone
to meet with you,

315
00:20:41,167 --> 00:20:42,600
but your aunt
insisted on coming.

316
00:20:42,733 --> 00:20:43,867
She's worried about you.

317
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:45,267
Of course.

318
00:20:45,567 --> 00:20:47,900
Jalil, how are your wounds?

319
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:48,867
Are they healed?

320
00:20:48,867 --> 00:20:50,333
(In Tausug) Thank you, Auntie.

321
00:20:50,567 --> 00:20:52,467
(In Tagalog)
But don't worry about me.

322
00:20:53,567 --> 00:20:55,367
What can I do to help you?

323
00:20:55,967 --> 00:21:00,367
Uncle, the men
who attacked our village

324
00:21:00,367 --> 00:21:02,133
are inside NLEA headquarters.

325
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:04,167
I need to get inside.

326
00:21:04,467 --> 00:21:05,433
What?

327
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:07,900
Jalil, what you're planning
is dangerous.

328
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:09,800
I know it's dangerous, but...

329
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,567
this is the only way
I can think of

330
00:21:11,567 --> 00:21:14,533
to bring Father back
as soon as possible.

331
00:21:14,767 --> 00:21:16,700
That is impossible.

332
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:19,367
What will you do
if they catch you?

333
00:21:19,533 --> 00:21:21,200
This is the only way,
Uncle.

334
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,367
This is the only way
to find my father.

335
00:21:23,367 --> 00:21:26,900
They may have the answers
to my questions.

336
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,533
Why Father?

337
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:33,667
Why was he accused
and arrested?

338
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:34,867
Why did they abduct him?

339
00:21:36,067 --> 00:21:37,333
Maybe...

340
00:21:38,033 --> 00:21:40,000
Maybe the syndicate
he went up against on the island

341
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,633
is retaliating.

342
00:21:42,867 --> 00:21:45,900
If they could do
something like that,

343
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:49,800
then they must have someone
working for them

344
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,500
inside the NLEA.

345
00:21:51,633 --> 00:21:58,600
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

346
00:22:02,733 --> 00:22:03,700
Jalil,

347
00:22:03,967 --> 00:22:08,267
Jamilah has already
started her new job.

348
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:11,233
(In Arabic)
Praise Allah.

349
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:13,767
That's good.

350
00:22:13,767 --> 00:22:15,833
That will keep her busy

351
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:19,033
and distract her
from what's happening to Father.

352
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:23,967
Jalil, that cop who
came to our neighborhood,

353
00:22:25,100 --> 00:22:28,633
we've noticed him
circling the area.

354
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:34,967
We are sure
he's out to get you.

355
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:37,367
Be extra careful, Jalil.

356
00:22:42,667 --> 00:22:45,900
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

357
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:46,967
[AMBULANCE SIREN WAILING]

358
00:22:46,967 --> 00:22:48,833
[TERESA] Have you administered
their medication?

359
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:49,833
[NURSE] Yes, Doc.

360
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:54,067
Doc, please check Bed No. 3.

361
00:22:54,933 --> 00:22:56,733
Doc, how's the ward?

362
00:22:56,933 --> 00:22:58,333
How's the triage?

363
00:22:58,600 --> 00:22:59,433
It's toxic.

364
00:22:59,733 --> 00:23:02,067
A lot of patients are
still waiting for evaluation.

365
00:23:03,667 --> 00:23:06,467
She's our new nurse, Doc.

366
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:15,733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:23:18,833 --> 00:23:21,733
Doctor, nice to meet you.

368
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,833
My name is Jamilah.

369
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:29,067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

370
00:23:29,067 --> 00:23:30,967
Welcome to the team, Jamilah.

371
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:32,900
I hope you stick around.

372
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:36,133
You know how cutthroat
it is here in the ER.

373
00:23:36,133 --> 00:23:38,600
Don't worry, Doctor.

374
00:23:38,967 --> 00:23:40,667
I don't give up easily.

375
00:23:41,067 --> 00:23:42,367
That's good to know.
I need to go.

376
00:23:42,567 --> 00:23:46,133
I just need to see what's
causing the delay at admissions.

377
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:47,967
- Okay.
- Good luck, Jamilah.

378
00:23:47,967 --> 00:23:53,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

379
00:23:53,967 --> 00:23:56,133
<i>Alright, son.
Be careful.</i>

380
00:23:57,767 --> 00:24:00,467
<i>Omar, my son
is coming home.</i>

381
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:02,367
<i> He's from SID.</i>

382
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:09,800
[JAMILAH]<i> I'm not giving up
</i> on helping Jalil.

383
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:11,833
<i>I'm not giving up
on finding Father.</i>

384
00:24:12,167 --> 00:24:16,067
<i>Your son, Marcus,
will lead us to where he is.</i>

385
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:18,633
<i> And you, Doctor...</i>

386
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:22,600
<i>you will be the way
to get closer to him.</i>

387
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:29,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC SWELLS, FADES]

388
00:24:34,933 --> 00:24:37,867
<i>Sir, any update on
Datu Rahman's whereabouts?</i>

389
00:24:37,867 --> 00:24:40,600
<i>I think I would love
to hear a word from you.</i>

390
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:42,967
<i>You will pay for
what you've done to us.</i>

391
00:24:42,967 --> 00:24:45,467
<i>What's the status on
the search for Datu Rahman?</i>

392
00:24:45,467 --> 00:24:47,767
<i> He was held captive
at the Dapayan Compound</i>

393
00:24:47,767 --> 00:24:48,900
<i>before he was transferred
to ZylveriX.</i>

394
00:24:49,067 --> 00:24:51,933
<i> Agent Reyes,
any leads</i> on Datu Rahman?

395
00:24:51,933 --> 00:24:53,767
<i>That was his
last known location.</i>

396
00:24:53,767 --> 00:24:56,400
Of all the people in the world,
<i> why Datu Rahman?</i>

397
00:24:56,533 --> 00:24:58,667
<i>Why did they
need to abduct him?</i>

398
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:03,967
<i> You must submit
a progress</i> report

399
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,867
<i> before midnight!</i>

400
00:25:06,967 --> 00:25:08,367
<i> Vinluan, Condecido...</i>

401
00:25:08,567 --> 00:25:10,733
<i>you will need a lot of
courage and determination.</i>

402
00:25:10,733 --> 00:25:13,200
<i>I'm sure you'll
both go far.</i>

403
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,033
<i> Have you heard of  ZylveriX?</i>

404
00:25:15,233 --> 00:25:17,100
<i>Cars are constantly
going in and out of there.</i>

405
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:18,767
[HORN HONKS]

406
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:20,067
<i> Stupid!</i>

407
00:25:20,667 --> 00:25:23,233
<i>I don't know if
it's connected to Datu Rahman.</i>

408
00:25:23,433 --> 00:25:27,233
<i>Any information that
can lead me to Father,</i>

409
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:28,967
<i> I'll take it.</i>
